  "notes": [
    "This case report describes a rare presentation of pheochromocytoma-induced pseudo-Cushing's syndrome, which has not been previously reported in the literature according to the authors.",
    "The diagnosis was confirmed through negative ACTH and CRH immunostaining, distinguishing it from ectopic ACTH secretion.",
    "The proposed mechanism involves catecholamine-induced hypermetabolism leading to HPA axis activation and a positive feedback loop involving cortisol and catecholamine production."
  ]
